    "Reason : 1 - The proposal, by nature of its use and its proximity to residential premises would be inappropriate development in this location leading to noise and general disturbance and nuisance to the adjoining residential occupiers which would be harmful to their amenities. The proposal would therefore be contrary to The National Planning Policy Framework (2021), policies D13(c) and D14 of the London Plan (2021) and DM38.A(b) of the Harrow Development Management Policies Local Plan (2013).",
    "Reason : 2 - The proposal failures to provide adequate details relating to car parking provision or servicing to serve the banqueting facility, the use would significantly intensify site usage and generated trips. The associated likely on site congestion and parking overspill into the London Borough of Harrow, with particular reference to the residential streets to the south of the site, is therefore considered to be detrimental to highway and pedestrian safety, and the amenities of neighbouring occupiers, contrary to the National Planning Policy Framework (2021), Policy T4 of The London Plan (2021),  and policies DM1 D (h), DM 42 E and F and DM44 of the Harrow Development Management policies Local Plan (2013)."
